"Kelechizy App (version 0.2) is a mobile app about Kelechizy. It is curated stuff about kc including education, experience, contact and a blog feed. This fixed minor bug in previous versions. Compatible on Android and Windows Phone.\nTechnology : HTML, CSS, JS and PhoneGap"
Meet The Employers is a career based workshop by GINA Consulting, designed to explore the missing elements in graduates and give them insights to what employers are looking for. Collaborated in the Full-Stack development of the website, design, SEO, SMO and Tech support.
Co-developed with my fellow ICT CDS team to create a website for NYSC Ondo State, Akure. Focused on design, content and user experience testing. Launched in July 2nd 2015 and currently maintained by the current executives.
OnGold Resources Limited is a trading company specialized in Real Estate, Import / Export and Merchandising in Nigeria. Engaged in the design of a modern professional website for the company.
VPoll is an online voting web application for polls, survey and nominations. Create polls (private, public or grouped), Share link to friends, Embed polls on any website and View results whenever wherever. Developed with PHP and MySql.
QuoteFrame is a web widget used to display random motivational quotes of influential people. Its first release was an IFrame widget, you just copy an paste the HTML code to your website. Tested with my friends blog and later became obsolete.
Lagos Laidbac is an urban merchandise company that engages in the production of Shirts, Caps and Phone Accessories. Collaborated in development of LLB\'s first website and now completely redesigned and managed by the team.
Mind Messenger is a desktop app that uses LAN for messaging and file transfer. A Windows based application built as an Industrial Training Project with C#.
LAN Messenger is a desktop app and web service. It was developed with C#(desktop) and PHP(web) to handle file upload and communication through a Local Server. #Clients
Engaged in website design of National Association of Computer Science Students (NACOSS), Unilag. Powered by Wordpress and awesome wp-plugins.
